the study groups in terms of serum log-claudin-5 levels [F
(1,115)¼ 5.841, p ¼ 0.017, gp
2 ¼ 0.048]. However, there was no
significant difference between the study groups in terms of serum
zonulin levels [F (1,115)¼ 0.530, p ¼ 0.468, gp
2 ¼ 0.005] (Table 3).
There was a significantly positive correlation between serum
zonulin levels and age (r ¼ 0.218, p ¼ 0.017) and BMI percentile
(r ¼ 0.597, p < 0.001) besides there was a significantly positive cor-
relation between serum claudin-5 levels and BMI percentile
(r ¼ 0.187, p ¼ 0.041) in whole study group. Also, the correlations
between the mean scores of total and subscale scores of RCADS-
CV, SDQ, SRS questionnaires, parent and teacher-rated T-DSM-IV-S
and serum zonulin and claudin-5 levels in the ADHD patient
group were examined. There was a significantly positive correl-
ation between serum zonulin levels and BMI percentile (r ¼ 0.607,
